review_blob: A "hit or miss" beer;  vinegar may taint BWs taste (they clean their equipment with it). Lame overall. Go Canadian.
A large mug of Labatt Blue is the perfect beer to have after youve just polished off a Molson and a shot of Canadian Club.  Im proud of my wannabe Canadian status.
My other fave Molson beer.  Ive read that Canada cares more about quality than quantity when it comes to beer.  America and it mega-production beer producers  should take note.
I was drinking a very shitty Budweiser (tap), I couldnt even finish it, so I asked the barmaid for a Molson Golden;  MG was like heaven in a glass. Now  I drink nothing but Canadian beer and whiskey.
